doc.previous: Birgenair puts in check the Boeing's 757 Maintenance Manual, regarding to the period in which the pitots can stay uncovered: "Despite these irritating and even conflicting procedures set forth in Boeing's 757 Maintenance Manual and the Maintenance Planning Document, a blockage of the pitot-tube might occur even within any period of stay on the ground should therefore be clearly required for all periods of stay on the ground."[10]
